==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shelving
<hw>Shelv"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sloping gradually; inclining;
<as>as, a <ex>shelving</ex> shore</as>.</def> <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Shelving</xex> arches.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shelving</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shelving
<hw>Shelv"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of fitting up
shelves; <as>as, the job of <ex>shelving</ex> a closet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of laying on a shelf, or on the shelf;
putting off or aside; <as>as, the <ex>shelving</ex> of a
claim</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Material for shelves; shelves,
collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shelvy</ent>⟦br⟧
